 formal ceremonial of unveiling, and, as in the case of [[Charles George Gordon|General Gordon]], [[Arthur Penrhyn Stanley|Dean Stanley]], and the [[Benjamin Disraeli|Earl of Beaconsfield]], the memorial was placed, a possession for ever, in the presence of none save those by whom the work was done.\" ''The Times'', 3 June 1895, p. 6</ref>\n| Poet\n|-\n| [[File:Connop Thirlwall NPG.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Connop Thirlwall]]\n| 1797\n| 1875\n| 78\n| ...\n| Bishop and historian\n|-\n| ...\n| [[Thomas Triplett|Thomas Triplet]]\n| 1602\n| 1670\n| 68\n| ...\n| Prebendary\n|-\n| ...\n| Owen Tudor\n| 1429\n| 1501\n| 71\u201372\n| ...\n| Monk of Westminster\n|-\n| [[File:Mrs garrick.PNG|100px]]\n| [[Eva Marie Veigel]]\n| 1724\n| 1822\n| 98\n| ...\n| Dancer\n|}\n\n==Memorials==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Image\n! Name\n! Born\n! Died\n! Age at death\n! Year<br>commemorated\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Details of<br>memorial\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Occupation\n|-\n| [[File:Joseph Addison by Sir Godfrey Kneller, Bt cleaned.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Joseph Addison]]\n| 1672\n| 1719\n| 47\n| 1809\n| Statue\n| Poet and essayist\n|-\n| [[File:Christopher Anstey with his daughter by William Hoare.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Christopher Anstey]]\n| 1724\n| 1805\n| 80\n| 1807\n| Stone tablet\n| Poet and author\n|-\n| [[File:Matthew Arnold - Project Gutenberg eText 16745.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Matthew Arnold]]\n| 1822\n| 1888\n| 65\n| 1989\n| Memorial bust & Mural tablet\n| Poet\n|-\n| [[File:Actrice Peggy Ashcroft op Schiphol voor optreden in Stadsschouwburg, Bestanddeelnr 914-0309.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Peggy Ashcroft]]\n| 1907\n| 1991\n| 83\n| 2005\n| Floor stone\n| Actress\n|-\n| [[File:AudenVanVechten1939.jpg|100px]]\n| [[W. H. Auden]]\n| 1907\n| 1973\n| 66\n| 1974\n| Floor stone\n| Poet\n|-\n| [[File:CassandraAusten-JaneAusten(c.1810) hires.jpg|100px]]\n| [[Jane Austen]]\n| 1775\n| 1817\n| 41\n| 1967\n| Wall tablet\n| Author\n|-\n| [[File:Sir John Betjeman (